{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17592577","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17592577"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T10:16:51+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T10:16:51+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15264"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15264","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15264"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.18,0.23,0.14,0.27,0.18]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7955"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116588"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7955","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7955"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15264"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98581"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19363"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19366"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22040"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116588","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/116588"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EGastric adenocarcinoma can be classified into two main subtypes based on their growth patterns and microscopic appearance.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is characteristic of diffuse gastric adenocarcinoma?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Demonstrates intestinal metaplasia","Mainly affects younger age groups","Predominantly affects men","Presents with ulcerated lesions","Shows glandular formation"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDiffuse gastric adenocarcinoma has distinct characteristics that differentiate it from intestinal-type gastric cancer. \u003Cstrong\u003EMainly affects younger age groups\u003C/strong\u003E is the correct answer as this subtype is typically seen in patients under the age of 40 years, in contrast to intestinal-type gastric adenocarcinoma which predominantly affects older patients.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDemonstrates intestinal metaplasia\u003C/strong\u003E is not a feature of diffuse gastric adenocarcinoma; instead, it is associated with loss of E-cadherin and lacks the intestinal metaplasia seen in intestinal-type gastric cancer. \u003Cstrong\u003EPredominantly affects men\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as diffuse gastric adenocarcinoma shows equal gender distribution, unlike intestinal-type which has a male predominance. \u003Cstrong\u003EPresents with ulcerated lesions\u003C/strong\u003E does not characterise this subtype, which instead shows diffuse thickening of the stomach wall creating a leather-bottle appearance (linitis plastica) rather than discrete ulcerated masses. \u003Cstrong\u003EShows glandular formation\u003C/strong\u003E is not typical of diffuse gastric adenocarcinoma, which is composed of poorly cohesive single cells that infiltrate the stomach wall rather than forming organised glandular structures.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Diffuse gastric adenocarcinoma typically affects younger patients under 40 years","Diffuse gastric adenocarcinoma presents with thickened, leather-bottle stomach appearance rather than ulceration"],"references":["Ajani JA, Lee J, Sano T, Janjigian YY, Fan D, Song S. Gastric adenocarcinoma. Nat Rev Dis Primers. 2017 Jun 1;3:17036. doi: 10.1038/nrdp.2017.36. PMID: 28569272","Menon G, El-Nakeep S, Babiker HM. Gastric Cancer. [Updated 2024 Oct 28]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK459142/","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98581"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15264"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"98581","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/98581"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-30T01:57:31+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-30T01:57:44+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7955"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"116588"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","i